# Lin Language TODO
# Format: [ ] pending  [/] in progress  [x] done
# Tiers: 🔴 blocking  🟡 important  🟢 nice-to-have

# Architecture reference (PICR — Reversible Polarized Interaction Combinators):
#   pic.graph  → abstract combinator graph (γ⁺ γ⁻ δ H L ω R + boundaries)
#   pic.reduce → scheduling-aware reduction ops (annihilate/dup/uncompute/log_state/
#                                                 fire_op/reverse_vector/log_bond)
#   pic.runtime→ CPU/GPU dispatch (cpu_dispatch, gpu_batch, gpu_batch_reverse,
#                                  uncompute_sweep, sync_point)
#
# Node set (7 nodes):
#   γ⁺  Constructor   principal(+), aux(left, right)
#   γ⁻  Destructor    principal(-), aux(left, right)
#   δ   Duplicator    principal(*), aux(left, right)
#   H   History       replaces ε; folds dead subgraphs into boundary history log
#   L   Log-Bond      passive ghost deposited at annihilation splice sites
#   ω   Operation     principal(+/-), aux(inputs..., outputs...)
#   R   Reverse-Vec   signal node; propagates backward rewrites through subgraph
#
# 4 Rules (reversible form):
#   Rule 1 — Reversible Annihilation (γ⁺ ⋈ γ⁻ → splice + deposit L-bond)
#   Rule 2 — Duplication (δ ⋈ γ⁺; reverse requires sync barrier at δ on backward pass)
#   Rule 3 — Reversible Uncomputation (R signal replaces ε sweep; runs subgraph backward)
#   Rule 4 — Congruence (inside boundaries; merge node carries origins attr for reverse split)
# Rules should be mostly user-defined via a lookup table.
# Goal: CPU, GPU, and high-perf GPU shaders — unified reversible pipeline via MLIR.
#
# 4 Invariants:
#   1. Linearity of principal ports
#   2. Boundary interface consistency
#   3. Confluence
#   4. Conservation of Topological Information — no rewrite may reduce graph information
#      entropy; every destructive step logs its delta or pairs with an R signal

## 🔴 Tier 0 — Architecture (foundational correctness)

# CPU/GPU Unification Strategy:
# The goal is to implement every reduction rule ONCE in the target-independent
# pic.reduce dialect using scf + arith + memref dialects (no llvm.*), then rely
# on MLIR's existing conversion passes to lower to:
#   • LLVM IR (CPU via ConvertToLLVMPass)
#   • SPIR-V / PTX (GPU via ConvertToSPIRVPass / GPU dialect)
# This means A1b is the central fix — all other "b" items are cleanup work that
# becomes natural once the reduction logic lives in the right dialect.
# Items 31, A4b, 21b, A2b, A3b are all sub-problems of finishing A1b correctly.
#
# Three architectural constraints hold throughout pic.reduce for unification:
#   C1. STATIC OPCODE DISPATCH — no function pointers (SPIR-V has none)
#   C2. HOST-ALLOCATED ARENA   — no malloc inside kernels (illegal on GPU)
#   C3. ω GPU ELIGIBILITY      — payloads restricted to SPIR-V-legal dialects

