[x] A5. PICR node set (H, L, R) in pic.graph dialect ✅
        # Foundational prerequisite for all reversibility. Blocks A6, A7, A8, item 18, item 21.
        - Add agentType values: HIS (H), LOG (L), RVEC (R) to PicGraph_AgentOp
        - H node: no principal interaction; accumulates a history_chain attribute pointing
          into the enclosing boundary's history log; replaces ε for boundary-scoped GC
        - L node: passive, no ports fired; carries {node_a_idx, node_b_idx} back-pointer
          to the originating γ⁺/γ⁻ pair; sits on spliced wires after annihilation
        - R node: principal(*), aux(next) — propagates through a subgraph forcing each
          encountered node to execute its rewrite rule in reverse
        - Update PicGraphDialect.td and PicGraphDialect.cpp
        - Update node encoding constants in LoweringPasses.cpp (NODE_HIS, NODE_LOG, NODE_RVEC)
        - Add to A2 rule lookup table: default dispatch entries for H, L, R interactions

[x] A6. Reversible Annihilation — L-bond deposition in pic.reduce ✅
        # Prerequisite: A5
        - Modify PicReduceToRuntimePass: annihilate now emits pic_reduce.log_bond at splice
          site instead of vanishing the γ⁺/γ⁻ pair entirely
        - Add PicReduce_LogBondOp to PicReduceDialect.td
          arguments: (node_a_idx: i32, node_b_idx: i32) — enough to reconstruct the pair
        - L node sits passively on the spliced wires; carries the log_bond payload
        - Forward path cost: O(1) — same as classic annihilation plus one extra node slot
        - Reverse path: R signal hitting an L node reads the payload and reconstructs the
          γ⁺/γ⁻ pair, restoring the original wiring
        - Invariant 4 enforcement: this is the mechanism that satisfies "log your delta"

[x] A7. Reversible Uncomputation — R signal propagation (replaces ε sweep) ✅
        # Prerequisite: A5, A6
        # This replaces item 18 (Node GC / arena reset) for boundary-scoped memory.
        - Add PicReduce_ReverseVectorOp to PicReduceDialect.td
        - Add pic_reduce.uncompute op: inverts a specific node pair using its log payload
        - Add pic_reduce.log_state op: pushes a structural delta token to the boundary history log
        - R signal dispatch rules added to worker_thread (alongside existing annihilation dispatch):
            R ⋈ γ⁺  → R on each aux port
            R ⋈ γ⁻  → R on each aux port
            R ⋈ ω   → cancel op, R on each aux port
            R ⋈ δ   → R on each aux port (sync barrier required — see item 20b)
            R ⋈ L   → read log_bond payload, reconstruct γ⁺/γ⁻, continue R propagation
            R ⋈ H   → replay H's history log backward, free chain, dissolve H node
        - Outside boundaries: ε erasure path kept as the fast non-logging fallback
        - Inside boundaries: R signal is emitted instead of ε when a branch becomes dead

