[ ] 18. Node GC / arena reset
        # PICR note: inside boundaries, GC is replaced by R-signal uncomputation (A7).
        # This item covers the fast non-boundary path and arena lifecycle.
        #
        # ⚠️ SPEC DEVIATION: Architecture.md definitively eliminates ε ("Why no ε?
        # In PICR, the History node (H) replaces it."). However the current implementation
        # retains NODE_ERA=4 (LoweringPasses.cpp:131) and uses ε for the non-boundary GC
        # fast path (line 358). ε outside boundaries is also emitted in item 4d fix
        # (proj_N eraser). The long-term goal per spec is to eliminate ε entirely, but
        # the current approach uses ε as a pragmatic fast path where full reversibility
        # isn't required inside hot non-boundary paths.
        - Outside boundaries: ε erasure propagation remains the fast GC path (parallel sweep)
        - Inside boundaries: H nodes + R signal handle GC via B4 cycle (A8) — no ε emitted
        - Arena reset after full reduction epoch for long-running programs
          # Currently: LoweringPasses.cpp:1733-1744 mallocs 128MB for net and queue once
          # at startup and never resets. Long-running programs will OOM as the allocator
          # (atomic fetch-add on alL, line 1741) never wraps or reclaims.
        - GPU GC: thousands of R/ε nodes propagate simultaneously via gpu.launch
        - Prerequisite for boundary GC path: A7, A8

